<subSubSection id="C32E65595CEEFF4A48A6FEF9FE84FE57" pageId="241" pageNumber="242" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B36D25CEEFF4A48A6FEF9FE84FE57" blockId="241.[151,1436,222,427]" pageId="241" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CEEFF4A48A6FEF9FEF5FEC2" bold="true" box="[199,315,294,319]" pageId="241" pageNumber="242">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was mistransferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CEEFF4A4A85FEF8FC95FEC3" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1905" box="[740,859,295,318]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="241" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CEEFF4A4A85FEF8FC95FEC3" box="[740,859,295,318]" italics="true" pageId="241" pageNumber="242">Anisepyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B235CEEFF4A4BECFEF9FB2CFEC2" box="[909,1250,294,319]" pageId="241" pageNumber="242" refId="ref282011" refString="Waichert, C. &amp; Azevedo, C. O. (2009) Phylogenetic analysis of Rhabdepyris (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae) and redefinition of generic limits based on structural characters. Zootaxa, 2284, 1 - 29." type="journal article">Waichert &amp; Azevedo. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, because it was misunderstood as belonging to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CEEFF4A4AD8FE95FC80FE9E" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1906" box="[697,846,330,355]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Trichotepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="241" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CEEFF4A4AD8FE95FC80FE9E" box="[697,846,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="241" pageNumber="242">Trichotepyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, probably by 
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CEEFF4A4C61FE95FB89FE9E" box="[1024,1095,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="241" pageNumber="242">lapsus</emphasis>
. This species, however, fits perfectly with 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CEEFF4A495BFEB1FD95FE7A" authority="Kieffer, 1905" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1905" box="[314,603,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Chlorepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="241" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CEEFF4A495BFEB1FE71FE7A" box="[314,447,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="241" pageNumber="242">Chlorepyris</emphasis>
Kieffer, 1905
</taxonomicName>
where it was originally described, back when 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CEEFF4A4C03FEB1FB29FE7A" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1905" box="[1122,1255,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Chlorepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="241" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CEEFF4A4C03FEB1FB29FE7A" box="[1122,1255,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="241" pageNumber="242">Chlorepyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CEEFF4A48D4FE4DFE8CFE56" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1904" box="[181,322,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Rhabdepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="241" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CEEFF4A48D4FE4DFE8CFE56" box="[181,322,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="241" pageNumber="242">Rhabdepyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
